#X text 1404 284 HITTING RECORD WILL PLAY THE OSCILLATOR AT CURRENTY SET FREQUENCY (UPPER THRESHOLD OF ONE OF THE BANDS) FROM PHASE 0 IT WILL PUT INTO ONE OF THE ARRAYS BASED ON WHAT IS INLETTED TO IT --- I CAN ADD ANOTHER INLET OR GUI BANG TO SAVE TO DISK WITH PROPER NAME SETTING \; NOTE: BEFORE RECORDING ONLY OSCILLATOR 0 SHOULD BE ON! \;;
#X obj 26 700 cnv 20 200 80 empty empty empty 20 12 0 12 #ff8300 #404040 0;
#X obj 28 729 *~ 1, f 5;
#X msg 60 705 0.667;
#X text 42 748 NORMALIZATION DUR TO 4 ENVELOPED OSCILLATOR, f 22;
#X obj 216 910 output~;
#X floatatom 73 729 5 0 0 0 - - - 0;
#X text 1087 36 - IN GENERAL ITS GOOD TO HAVE AN ANTI-ALIASING FILTER WHEN RECORDING \, AROUND 20000[Hz] \; - DO I NEED TO FADE-IN/OUT IN AUDACITY BEFORE BRINGING TO PD? ----> NO NEED \, SINCE THE HANN ENVELOPE WILL DO THE TASK OF ZERO-FADING \; - THE QUESTION IS: SHOULD I DO THE ANALYSIS AND RESYNTHESIS ON ONE OR MULTI-OSCILLATOR WAVETABLE? -----> SEEMS LIKE THAT IT WILL NOT AFFECT THE EXISTING HARMONICS SINCE THE ADDITION IS A LINEAR SYSTEM. BUT TO TEST BOTH \; - H_MAX = (NYQUIST-FREQUENCY = 24000)/(MAX f0 WANT TO PLAY) \; - EXPORT 3 DIFFERENT WAVETABLE FROM THE ORIGINAL ONE \; ---> 1) LOW NOTES (UPTO 200Hz): INT(24000/200) = 120 => UPTO 120-(20) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \; ---> 2) MIDDLE NOTES (UPTO 1000Hz) :INT(24000/1000) = 24 => UPTO 24-(4) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \; ---> 3) HIGH NOTES (UPTO 4000Hz): INT(24000/4000) = 6 => UPTO 6-(1) HARMONICS ABOVE 300 ARE ALLOWABLE \;, f 112;
#X text 779 722 DONT BE STUPID! KNOW WHAT YOURE DOING! FFT SIZE COULD ONLY BE EQUAL TO SAMPLE(WAVE) SIZE IF YOU WANT TO SEE THE SPECTRUM!, f 62;
#X text 778 802 FIND/MAKE A BETTER WAVE \, CUT FROM SAMPLE OR MAKE A BAND-LIMITED WAVEFORM TUTORIAL TO GET MORE IDEA!, f 52;
#X text 777 770 CHECK YOUR NOTES! --> UNFUCK YOUR BRAIN!;
#X text 779 861 ALSO MAYBE A BETTER IDEA TO ENVELOPE - AT CONTROL RATE - THE WAVE BEFORE FEEDING IT TO THE WAVE-PLAYER (OSCILLATOR);
#X text 777 926 THE WHOLE IDEA OF (MULTI) BAND-LIMITED FILTERING IS TO NOT GO ABOVE NYQUIST FREQUENCY - 24000Hz - AS INPUT(MIDI) FREQUENCY GOES HIGHER, f 71;
